            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>itus</ex></expan> Aeli<supplied reason="lost">us Hadrianus</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Antoninus <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">Pius <expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>m<supplied reason="lost">a</supplied>x</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">--- co(n)s(ul) --- p(ater)? p(atriae)</supplied> <lb n="4"/>bal<supplied reason="lost">in</supplied>eum vetus<supplied reason="lost">tate conlapsum</supplied> <lb n="5"/>sua pecunia <supplied reason="lost">restituit</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Buchstabenhöhe bezieht sich auf Zeile 2. Horster: Z. 2/3: Zeilenfall nicht angegeben; Z. 3: max. Datierung: Wenn die Ergänzung p(ater) p(atriae) in Z. 3 richtig ist, kann die Inschrift erst aus der Zeit ab dem 1./7.1.139 n. Chr. stammen</p>
            </div>
